1
00:01:41,009 --> 00:01:44,270
[A Moment But Forever]

2
00:01:44,920 --> 00:01:47,220
[Episode 16]

3
00:01:52,470 --> 00:01:53,390
It's getting dark.

4
00:01:53,390 --> 00:01:54,070
Shouldn't we

5
00:01:54,070 --> 00:01:55,350
find a place to stay for the night?

6
00:01:57,110 --> 00:01:58,310
There's a house ahead.

7
00:02:06,390 --> 00:02:07,710
I never expected

8
00:02:07,710 --> 00:02:08,470
to see you

9
00:02:08,470 --> 00:02:10,030
again so soon, sir.

10
00:02:11,150 --> 00:02:11,870
I knew

11
00:02:11,870 --> 00:02:13,390
you'd come to my place.

12
00:02:13,630 --> 00:02:14,390
Come in.

13
00:02:14,390 --> 00:02:15,110
Come on, come on.

14
00:02:15,110 --> 00:02:15,860
Come in.

15
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:20,480
[Library]

16
00:02:26,750 --> 00:02:27,550
Is it

17
00:02:27,550 --> 00:02:29,260
usually just you here, sir?

18
00:02:29,390 --> 00:02:30,030
Yes.

19
00:02:30,030 --> 00:02:31,829
I am the caretaker of this library.

20
00:02:31,829 --> 00:02:33,310
You can call me Bao.

21
00:02:34,150 --> 00:02:35,070
This library

22
00:02:35,070 --> 00:02:36,560
looks quite old.

23
00:02:36,670 --> 00:02:38,590
I wonder when it was built.

24
00:02:38,770 --> 00:02:39,930
Oh, that was a long time ago.

25
00:02:40,470 --> 00:02:42,480
Back then, when the Mute Goddess of Wu Mountain

26
00:02:42,700 --> 00:02:43,950
passed through this area,

27
00:02:43,950 --> 00:02:45,800
she saw the people living in poverty,

28
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:47,310
so she used her magic

29
00:02:48,370 --> 00:02:50,540
to instantly create this library

30
00:02:50,740 --> 00:02:53,230
to spread knowledge and enlighten the people.

31
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:54,550
If you really want to count the years,

32
00:02:55,030 --> 00:02:56,810
it's been several hundred years.

33
00:02:57,100 --> 00:02:58,350
The Mute of Wu Mountain?

34
00:02:58,380 --> 00:02:59,180
Yeah.

35
00:03:00,630 --> 00:03:02,390
You've heard of the Mute Goddess too?

36
00:03:03,140 --> 00:03:05,190
I've heard that she was very knowledgeable,

37
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:06,190
kind, and intelligent,

38
00:03:06,190 --> 00:03:06,870
and that she did a lot of

39
00:03:06,870 --> 00:03:08,270
good things for the people.

40
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,390
This book records

41
00:03:10,390 --> 00:03:11,670
many of her past deeds.

42
00:03:11,670 --> 00:03:12,870
How much can such a thin book

43
00:03:12,870 --> 00:03:14,270
really record?

44
00:03:14,430 --> 00:03:16,860
There are many legends about the Mute Goddess.

45
00:03:16,950 --> 00:03:18,110
When I have time later,

46
00:03:18,110 --> 00:03:19,510
I'll tell you all about them.

47
00:03:21,030 --> 00:03:23,150
There are over a hundred

48
00:03:23,150 --> 00:03:24,270
libraries like this in the Eastern Wilderness,

49
00:03:24,310 --> 00:03:26,400
all built by the Mute Goddess.

50
00:03:26,590 --> 00:03:27,829
The collections inside

51
00:03:27,950 --> 00:03:29,829
were all left by her.

52
00:03:29,870 --> 00:03:31,550
Too many to count.

53
00:03:33,070 --> 00:03:35,270
These are all treasures

54
00:03:35,350 --> 00:03:36,110
the Mute Goddess left for us

55
00:03:36,110 --> 00:03:38,230
to pass down from generation to generation.

56
00:03:38,470 --> 00:03:39,910
She was really amazing,

57
00:03:39,910 --> 00:03:40,900
not only helping common people

58
00:03:40,900 --> 00:03:42,230
by doing so many good deeds

59
00:03:42,390 --> 00:03:43,990
but also writing so many great books.

60
00:03:44,190 --> 00:03:45,000
Yes, indeed.

61
00:03:45,310 --> 00:03:46,110
Young lady,

62
00:03:47,270 --> 00:03:50,030
the Mute Goddess of Wu Mountain is a god.

63
00:03:51,110 --> 00:03:51,910
A god?

64
00:03:52,350 --> 00:03:53,150
Yeah.

65
00:03:53,390 --> 00:03:55,150
She descended from the heavens, riding a phoenix.

66
00:03:55,430 --> 00:03:56,270
Wherever she went,

67
00:03:56,270 --> 00:03:58,030
deserts transformed into lush oases.

68
00:03:58,490 --> 00:04:00,200
Vicious thugs would abandon their wicked ways

69
00:04:00,220 --> 00:04:01,630
upon seeing her,

70
00:04:02,430 --> 00:04:03,710
while the kind-hearted would

71
00:04:03,710 --> 00:04:05,240
receive blessings

72
00:04:05,490 --> 00:04:06,570
and good fortune.

73
00:04:07,070 --> 00:04:08,270
And the ignorant,

74
00:04:08,270 --> 00:04:09,870
those simple and foolish ones,

75
00:04:09,910 --> 00:04:11,840
would become extremely intelligent

76
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:13,710
the moment she touched their heads.

77
00:04:14,870 --> 00:04:16,029
But why

78
00:04:16,510 --> 00:04:17,829
is she called the Mute Goddess?

79
00:04:18,220 --> 00:04:19,070
Is it because...

80
00:04:19,709 --> 00:04:21,079
she couldn't speak?

81
00:04:21,790 --> 00:04:23,910
The Mute Goddess possessed boundless magical powers.

82
00:04:24,280 --> 00:04:25,470
Her words commanded reality.

83
00:04:25,510 --> 00:04:27,070
Whatever she said would come true.

84
00:04:27,430 --> 00:04:28,240
So,

85
00:04:29,350 --> 00:04:30,860
she rarely opened her mouth to speak.

86
00:04:32,820 --> 00:04:33,630
Isn't that a bit

87
00:04:33,630 --> 00:04:34,630
exaggerated?

88
00:04:34,630 --> 00:04:36,000
How am I exaggerating?

89
00:04:36,110 --> 00:04:37,710
Everything I said is true.

90
00:04:37,830 --> 00:04:39,270
It's all written in the books.

91
00:04:39,310 --> 00:04:39,990
Come on, come on.

92
00:04:39,990 --> 00:04:41,130
I'll find them and show you now.

93
00:04:41,150 --> 00:04:42,190
No need, no need.

94
00:04:42,230 --> 00:04:43,180
Reality and legend

95
00:04:43,180 --> 00:04:44,430
are two different things, after all.

96
00:04:44,630 --> 00:04:46,670
Reading it would just be a waste of time.

97
00:04:47,190 --> 00:04:48,350
So you're saying

98
00:04:48,350 --> 00:04:50,070
everything written in the books is false?

99
00:04:50,390 --> 00:04:52,390
This library sheltering you for the night

100
00:04:52,390 --> 00:04:53,300
is fake?

101
00:04:53,300 --> 00:04:54,550
Even all the good deeds

102
00:04:54,550 --> 00:04:55,430
that the Mute Goddess did

103
00:04:55,430 --> 00:04:56,710
are just made up?

104
00:04:58,630 --> 00:04:59,990
That's not what he meant.

105
00:05:00,010 --> 00:05:01,060
Then what did he mean?

106
00:05:01,430 --> 00:05:02,460
Since all the people of the Eastern Wilderness

107
00:05:02,460 --> 00:05:03,390
all tell these stories

108
00:05:03,630 --> 00:05:05,750
and are willing to worship the Mute Goddess,

109
00:05:05,990 --> 00:05:07,790
there must be a reason for it!

110
00:05:07,790 --> 00:05:08,390
Since you're now

111
00:05:08,390 --> 00:05:10,070
taking shelter in one of the libraries

112
00:05:10,070 --> 00:05:11,190
she built,

113
00:05:11,230 --> 00:05:12,710
you should respect her

114
00:05:12,710 --> 00:05:13,710
and be grateful to her!

115
00:05:14,670 --> 00:05:15,350
Bao,

116
00:05:15,350 --> 00:05:16,150
where are you going?

117
00:05:16,230 --> 00:05:17,150
Don't call me "Bao."

118
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:18,110
We're not that close.

119
00:05:18,110 --> 00:05:18,870
Wait,

120
00:05:18,910 --> 00:05:19,710
where are the rooms?

121
00:05:20,390 --> 00:05:22,070
Downstairs. Find it yourself!

122
00:05:27,230 --> 00:05:28,590
This is a storage room.

123
00:05:28,590 --> 00:05:30,230
This Bao is not being very hospitable.

124
00:05:30,780 --> 00:05:31,720
Just make do.

125
00:05:32,230 --> 00:05:33,150
Why complain so much?

126
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:34,070
Just now,

127
00:05:34,070 --> 00:05:35,310
why didn't you let me speak?

128
00:05:37,420 --> 00:05:38,460
I just thought

129
00:05:38,510 --> 00:05:39,230
that since we're

130
00:05:39,230 --> 00:05:40,390
staying at someone else's place,

131
00:05:40,390 --> 00:05:42,030
even if you don't want to agree with him,

132
00:05:42,030 --> 00:05:44,040
at least you shouldn't make him angry.

133
00:05:53,850 --> 00:05:55,240
I don't think she's acting.

134
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:57,040
She's probably not the Mute Lady of Wu Mountain.

135
00:06:29,870 --> 00:06:31,390
You've written this character wrong.

136
00:06:34,190 --> 00:06:34,990
Why are you

137
00:06:34,990 --> 00:06:36,390
standing behind me without making a sound?

138
00:06:36,390 --> 00:06:37,470
You startled me.

139
00:06:38,310 --> 00:06:39,190
I'm sorry.

140
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:40,750
I didn't mean to disturb you.

141
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:41,710
But

142
00:06:42,150 --> 00:06:44,390
you did write that character wrong.

143
00:06:47,830 --> 00:06:48,670
Impossible.

144
00:06:49,590 --> 00:06:51,159
I copied it from the book exactly.

145
00:06:52,710 --> 00:06:53,510
Look,

146
00:06:54,470 --> 00:06:55,430
that book of yours

147
00:06:55,430 --> 00:06:57,190
has been damaged by bookworms.

148
00:06:57,190 --> 00:06:59,150
This phrase should be

149
00:06:59,190 --> 00:07:00,350
"Winter ice can be broken;

150
00:07:00,550 --> 00:07:01,990
summer twigs can be tied."

151
00:07:02,350 --> 00:07:03,430
It means

152
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:05,270
that in winter, we obtain ice,

153
00:07:05,380 --> 00:07:07,220
while in summer, we can gather twigs.

154
00:07:08,250 --> 00:07:09,050
See,

155
00:07:09,070 --> 00:07:10,270
there's an extra dot here.

156
00:07:29,270 --> 00:07:30,470
You're right.

157
00:07:31,950 --> 00:07:33,150
I misread it.

158
00:07:34,030 --> 00:07:34,630
Well...

159
00:07:34,630 --> 00:07:35,350
Bao,

160
00:07:35,670 --> 00:07:36,950
you can't read?

161
00:07:37,150 --> 00:07:37,950
That's right.

162
00:07:38,870 --> 00:07:41,270
Then... how do you write?

163
00:07:41,310 --> 00:07:42,790
Just copy it exactly as I see it.

164
00:07:44,020 --> 00:07:44,700
I copied it wrong,

165
00:07:44,870 --> 00:07:45,950
and I've copied so much.

166
00:07:46,090 --> 00:07:47,880
I need to correct them quickly.

167
00:07:48,980 --> 00:07:50,350
Do you have to recopy everything?

168
00:07:51,350 --> 00:07:52,310
That's not necessary.

169
00:07:52,730 --> 00:07:54,650
I only copied this one character wrong.

170
00:07:55,060 --> 00:07:55,870
So,

171
00:07:56,790 --> 00:07:58,350
I just need to recopy this page

172
00:07:58,350 --> 00:08:00,190
and rebind it later.

173
00:08:00,870 --> 00:08:01,680
But

174
00:08:02,150 --> 00:08:03,270
if you can't read,

175
00:08:03,830 --> 00:08:04,710
why are you

176
00:08:04,710 --> 00:08:06,060
copying these books?

177
00:08:06,710 --> 00:08:09,110
Although the Mute Goddess of Wu Mountain

178
00:08:09,110 --> 00:08:10,310
watches over us,

179
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:11,260
we still

180
00:08:11,260 --> 00:08:12,910
need to do our part.

181
00:08:13,390 --> 00:08:15,230
These books are very precious.

182
00:08:15,630 --> 00:08:16,670
These books are vulnerable

183
00:08:16,670 --> 00:08:17,870
to fire, moisture, and insects.

184
00:08:18,270 --> 00:08:19,390
So I figured

185
00:08:19,630 --> 00:08:20,870
I should make more copies.

186
00:08:21,550 --> 00:08:25,120
If they ever get damaged or destroyed,

187
00:08:25,790 --> 00:08:27,110
at least there will be backups.

188
00:08:27,350 --> 00:08:28,430
That way, the children won't

189
00:08:28,430 --> 00:08:29,670
be left without books to read, right?

190
00:08:30,550 --> 00:08:31,870
Even though

191
00:08:32,070 --> 00:08:34,070
fewer people read books these days,

192
00:08:34,230 --> 00:08:35,030
there will surely

193
00:08:35,590 --> 00:08:37,669
be more in the future.

194
00:08:38,789 --> 00:08:40,190
Then let me help you copy them.

195
00:08:41,510 --> 00:08:42,720
That's great!

196
00:08:44,830 --> 00:08:45,780
One piece for Yuanzhong.

197
00:08:46,310 --> 00:08:47,120
One piece for me.

198
00:08:47,830 --> 00:08:48,830
One piece for Zi Fei.

199
00:08:49,270 --> 00:08:50,070
One piece for me.

200
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:52,150
One piece for Ji Tanyin...

201
00:08:54,030 --> 00:08:54,830
You think you have too much?

202
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:56,750
No, whether it's too much or not is one thing,

203
00:08:56,750 --> 00:08:58,750
but is it appropriate to divide it like this?

204
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:00,470
Aren't I just dividing it in order?

205
00:09:00,550 --> 00:09:01,790
What order?

206
00:09:01,790 --> 00:09:02,990
My order.

207
00:09:33,910 --> 00:09:34,710
What's wrong?

208
00:09:34,740 --> 00:09:36,460
D-Did I write something wrong?

209
00:09:37,270 --> 00:09:38,110
Your handwriting...

210
00:09:38,990 --> 00:09:40,350
is very good.

211
00:09:42,790 --> 00:09:43,590
Wait a moment.

212
00:09:44,030 --> 00:09:45,430
Let me show you something nice.

213
00:10:01,550 --> 00:10:03,190
These are the original manuscripts

214
00:10:03,190 --> 00:10:04,870
left by the Mute Goddess of Wu Mountain.

215
00:10:05,030 --> 00:10:06,870
Only these few volumes remain now.

216
00:10:07,710 --> 00:10:08,510
Take a look.

217
00:10:19,870 --> 00:10:21,470
Right? Doesn't it look similar?

218
00:10:22,670 --> 00:10:24,110
Your handwriting

219
00:10:24,110 --> 00:10:25,230
is just like the Goddess's.

220
00:10:25,870 --> 00:10:27,430
Both are written very well.

221
00:10:33,350 --> 00:10:34,150
Bao.

222
00:10:35,470 --> 00:10:36,430
What was

223
00:10:37,270 --> 00:10:38,750
this place called before?

224
00:10:39,050 --> 00:10:40,200
Rammed Earth City.

225
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:42,350
That's not right.

226
00:10:43,110 --> 00:10:44,190
A long time ago,

227
00:10:44,990 --> 00:10:46,190
the river to the south

228
00:10:46,190 --> 00:10:47,310
hadn't split into multiple streams yet.

229
00:10:47,470 --> 00:10:48,830
Whenever there was heavy rain,

230
00:10:48,830 --> 00:10:50,550
it could potentially cause flooding.

231
00:10:51,190 --> 00:10:52,590
The landscape at that time...

232
00:10:55,150 --> 00:10:56,840
was quite different from what it is now.

233
00:10:57,210 --> 00:10:58,540
Oh, you mean back then?

234
00:11:00,190 --> 00:11:02,230
At that time, this place was called Chaotic Cloud Village.

235
00:11:02,540 --> 00:11:04,470
This area had strong winds and many clouds.

236
00:11:04,670 --> 00:11:06,350
The dark clouds in the sky...

237
00:11:06,990 --> 00:11:07,790
well...

238
00:11:08,190 --> 00:11:08,980
Anyway,

239
00:11:09,230 --> 00:11:10,630
it was very chaotic around here back then.

240
00:11:10,630 --> 00:11:12,270
That's why it got that name.

241
00:11:12,630 --> 00:11:14,550
Later, the Mute Goddess

242
00:11:14,710 --> 00:11:17,790
built the library using the rammed earth technique,

243
00:11:17,790 --> 00:11:19,550
and then more and more people settled here.

244
00:11:20,070 --> 00:11:21,820
So it was renamed Rammed Earth City.

245
00:11:26,250 --> 00:11:27,690
Chaotic Cloud Village...

246
00:11:35,350 --> 00:11:36,750
No wonder this place felt

247
00:11:36,750 --> 00:11:38,230
somewhat familiar on my way here.

248
00:11:38,910 --> 00:11:39,950
Chaotic Cloud Village...

249
00:11:40,260 --> 00:11:41,550
When I came here back then,

250
00:11:41,580 --> 00:11:43,070
there were only a dozen households.

251
00:11:43,270 --> 00:11:44,590
Those books were also mine.

252
00:11:45,030 --> 00:11:46,830
Could I be the Mute Lady of Wu Mountain?

253
00:11:47,670 --> 00:11:49,590
But why would they call me "Mute"?

254
00:11:50,140 --> 00:11:50,940
Oh, right.

255
00:11:51,190 --> 00:11:52,840
When I crossed the Sea of Flux back then,

256
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:53,830
I was severely injured.

257
00:11:53,850 --> 00:11:55,180
My throat hadn't recovered yet.

258
00:11:55,270 --> 00:11:56,670
So I was indeed both deaf and mute at that time.

259
00:11:57,030 --> 00:11:59,230
But I didn't ride a phoenix,

260
00:11:59,230 --> 00:12:00,830
nor did I have the power to make my words command reality.

261
00:12:07,190 --> 00:12:08,390
Why are you still up?

262
00:12:10,190 --> 00:12:11,230
I'm not tired yet.

263
00:12:11,390 --> 00:12:12,390
You weren't here just now.

264
00:12:12,590 --> 00:12:13,430
Where did you go?

265
00:12:14,590 --> 00:12:15,980
I went to copy books for Bao.

266
00:12:18,070 --> 00:12:19,200
Don't listen to his nonsense.

267
00:12:20,150 --> 00:12:21,390
The phoenix is a divine beast

268
00:12:21,670 --> 00:12:22,790
with a proud nature.

269
00:12:22,830 --> 00:12:23,510
It would never

270
00:12:23,510 --> 00:12:24,990
serve as a mount for anyone.

271
00:12:25,310 --> 00:12:26,110
That Mute Lady of Wu Mountain

272
00:12:26,110 --> 00:12:27,390
did have some power,

273
00:12:27,790 --> 00:12:29,110
but she was far from

274
00:12:29,110 --> 00:12:30,310
being able to command reality with her words

275
00:12:30,430 --> 00:12:31,990
or enlightening others with a mere touch to the head.

276
00:12:32,140 --> 00:12:33,700
Our clan also has some

277
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:35,130
legends about gods,

278
00:12:35,350 --> 00:12:36,790
but none as powerful

279
00:12:36,990 --> 00:12:37,950
as that.

280
00:12:39,430 --> 00:12:40,070
Then why

281
00:12:40,070 --> 00:12:41,430
do they still spread such stories?

282
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,230
So-called legends

283
00:12:45,550 --> 00:12:46,350
are nothing more than

284
00:12:46,350 --> 00:12:48,380
stories passed down orally by people.

285
00:12:48,670 --> 00:12:49,590
Since these are stories,

286
00:12:49,590 --> 00:12:50,310
there are

287
00:12:50,350 --> 00:12:52,470
some embellishments and exaggerations.

288
00:12:52,910 --> 00:12:54,310
To make the stories stand out,

289
00:12:54,350 --> 00:12:55,270
people add

290
00:12:55,270 --> 00:12:57,540
their own speculations and interpretations.

291
00:12:57,750 --> 00:12:58,710
As these stories spread from person to person,

